        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 1:01PM EDT by NWS Indianapolis IN</headline>
        <description>At 101 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Plainfield, or 13 miles west of Indianapolis, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Indianapolis, Plainfield, Avon, and Indianapolis Int'l Airport.

This includes Interstate 70 between mile markers 68 and 74.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
